 Serie A club Cagliari again escaped sanctions over alleged racist behaviour by their fans. This was after the league’s disciplinary tribunal decided on Tuesday not to take action over monkey noises aimed at Inter Milan’s Belgian forward Romelu Lukaku. The tribunal said in a statement on Tuesday that “in terms of dimension and real perception”, the chants could not be considered discriminatory under the league’s disciplinary code. “The tribunal has decided not to apply sanctions to Cagliari,” it said, referring to the incidents in the match on Sept 1. Continue reading Cagliari escape sanctions over Lukaku abuse at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard